\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b 1.                  Cicendia}             Adanson
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By †T.G. Tutin.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Annual herbs. Calyx campanulate, with 4 short, deltate lobes. Corolla with ovoid tube and 4 short lobes. Anthers basifixed, cordate, not twisting spirally after dehiscence. stigma peltate.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. C. filiformis} (L.) Delarbre, {\i Fl. Auvergne} ed. 2, 29 (1800) ({\i Microcala filiformis} (L.) Hoffmanns. & Link). Slender annual 3-14(-20) cm. Stems simple or with few branches. Leaves 2-6(-10) mm, linear, few, soon withering. Flowers 3-6 mm, yellow. Capsule 4-5 mm, ovoid. 2n = 26. {\i Damp, sandy or peaty places. S. & W. Europe.} Az Be Bl Br Co †Da Ga Ge Gr Hb Ho Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu.
\par

