\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By †T.G. Tutin.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Like {\i Cicendia} but calyx deeply divided into linear lobes; corolla-tube cylindrical; anthers ovate; stigma bifid.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. E. pusillum} (Lam.) Caruel in Parl., {\i Fl. Ital.}{\b  6:} 743 (1886) ({\i Cicendia pusilla} (Lam.) Griseb.). Slender, divaricately branched annual 1-12 cm. Leaves 2-12 mm, linear-lanceolate. Flowers 4-5 mm, pink or cream. Capsule 5-6 mm, fusiform. 2n = 20.{\i  Damp, sandy or grassy places. S.W. Europe}. Co Ga Hs It Lu Sa.
