\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. B. perfoliata} (L.) Hudson, {\i Fl. Angl.} 146 (1762) ({\i Chlora perfoliata} (L.) L.). Erect, glaucous annual 10-60 cm. Leaves 5-30 mm, ovate to triangular, the basal obtuse, not connate at base, the cauline acute, connate or rarely free at base. Flowers (6-)8-35 mm, yellow. Calyx-tube very short; lobes 6-12, linear to lanceolate. Lobes of the stigma erect at anthesis, becoming patent later. {\i W., S. & C. Europe.} Al Au Be Bl Br Bu Co Cr Cz Ga Ge Gr Hb He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Lu Rs (K) Sa Si Tu.
