\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  perfoliata} : Usually robust. Upper cauline leaves triangular, not or scarcely narrowed towards the base. Flowers 8-15 mm, 6- to 8-merous. Calyx-lobes linear, 1-veined. 2n = 40.{\i  Throughout most of the range of the species, but rare in the south}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp.{\b  serotina} (Koch ex Reichenb.) Vollmann,{\i  Fl. Bayern} 594 (1914) ({\i B. serotina} (Koch ex Reichenb.) G. Beck, {\i B. perfoliata} subsp.{\i  acuminata} (Koch & Ziz) Dostál,{\i  Chlora serotina} Koch ex Reichenb.): Usually slender. Upper cauline leaves distinctly narrowed towards the base. Flowers (6-)8-10 mm, 6- to 8-merous. Calyx-lobes linear-lanceolate, often 3-veined in lower part, 3-4 times as long as tube. 2n = 40.{\i  Usually inland. S. & C. Europe; Netherlands}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp.{\b  imperfoliata} (L. fil.) Franco & Rocha Afonso, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc. }{\b 64:} 378 (1971) ({\i Chlora imperfoliata} L. fil.). Like ({\b b}) but upper cauline leaves not or scarcely connate at base; calyx-lobes lanceolate, distinctly 3-veined, twice as long as tube. 2n = 20.{\i  Damp places near the sea, rarely inland. S.W. Europe extending to S. Italy and Sicilia}.
\par

